org.opendaylight.l2switch.hosttracker.plugin.internal

Class ConcurrentClusterAwareLinkHashMap<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.opendaylight.l2switch.hosttracker.plugin.internal.ConcurrentClusterAwareLinkHashMap<K,V>
  • Type Parameters:
    K - Must be a Link
    V - Must be org.opendaylight.l2switch.hosttracker.plugin.inventory.Link;
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    ConcurrentMap<K,V>, Map<K,V>

    public class ConcurrentClusterAwareLinkHashMap<K,V>
extends Object
implements ConcurrentMap<K,V>
    This will (try to) submit all writes and deletes in to the MD-SAL database. The removeLocally(org.opendaylight.yangtools.yang.binding.InstanceIdentifier) removeLocally(java.lang.Object) putLocally(org.opendaylight.yangtools.yang.binding.InstanceIdentifier, java.lang.Object) methods should be used when dataChanges are dealt locally and not update to MD-SAL.
